  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting national and regional capacities in reducing the risks posed by illicit weapons flows in the Caribbean and in Africa</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="DE">Unterst&#xFC;tzung nationaler und regionaler Kapazit&#xE4;ten zur Reduzierung der Risiken im Zusammenhang mit illegalen Waffenstr&#xF6;men in der Karibik und Afrika</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="DE">Beitrag zur Verbesserung der Wirksamkeit der Kontrollma&#xDF;nahmen der Partnerstaaten und regionalen Organisationen (insbesondere der CARICOM und der ECOWAS) im Hinblick auf die Bek&#xE4;mpfung des illegalen Waffen-, Munitions- und Sprengstoffhandels und die Erzielung einer deutlichen Verringerung der illegalen Waffenstr&#xF6;me bis 2030 mit Fokus auf die Karibik und Afrika.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhance the capacities of states and other relevant stakeholders to combat the proliferation, possession, and misuse of illicit arms, ammunition, and their components in Africa and the Caribbean.Survey plans to expand its work on Improvised Explosive Devices (IEDs) beyond the current focus on West Africa to cover other regions of the continent. Our research and analysis work would provide the evidence needed to enhance states and Regional Organizations&#x2019; capacities to design and implement counter-IED interventions.

In the Caribbean, the Survey plans is to respond to a request from and subsequent discussions with CARICOM IMPACS to support the implementation and evaluation of the &#x201C;Roadmap for addressing Caribbean priority actions on the illicit proliferation of firearms and ammunition across the Caribbean in a sustainable manner&#x201D; (&#x201C;Roadmap&#x201D;).</narrative>
  </description>
